# Git & GitHub

## Git

### Git kya hai

Git ek version control system hai.
Code changes track karta hai.

### Iska use kisliye hota hai

* Code history maintain karne ke liye
* Team collaboration ke liye
* Backup aur rollback ke liye

### Ye internally kaise kaam karta hai

Git snapshots store karta hai.
Har commit ek saved state hoti hai.

### Working Steps

Code change → git add → git commit → History save

### Mental Image / Analogy

Game save points jaisa.

### Real Engineer Usage

* Daily development
* Team collaboration
* Production fixes

### Common Commands

```bash
git init
git status
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git log
```

### Troubleshooting Thinking

* File staged hai?
* Wrong branch?
* Merge conflict?

### Communication Practice

* “Git code history maintain karta hai.”
* “Commits rollback aur collaboration easy banate hain.”
* “Production environments me Git essential tool hai.”

---

## GitHub

### GitHub kya hai

Online platform jaha Git repositories host hoti hain.

### Iska use kisliye hota hai

* Remote backup
* Team collaboration
* Pull requests
* CI/CD integration

### Ye internally kaise kaam karta hai

Local Git repo remote GitHub repo se sync hota hai.

### Working Steps

Local commit → git push → GitHub update → Team access

### Mental Image / Analogy

Cloud storage for code.

### Real Engineer Usage

* Team development
* Code reviews
* Open-source projects

### Common Commands

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
git push
git pull
```

### Troubleshooting Thinking

* Authentication fail?
* Remote branch mismatch?
* Push rejected?

### Communication Practice

* “GitHub collaborative development platform hai.”
* “Pull requests code review process improve karte hain.”

